1	/**
2	 * lab.commission-post-xguild / lab.wait-for-writ-terminal-xguild —
3	 * cross-guild scenario engines for trial workloads.
4	 *
5	 * The canonical trial scenario is "post a commission to the test guild
6	 * and wait for it to complete." `lab.commission-post-xguild` does both
7	 * inline by default (single engine fits the rig template's single-
8	 * scenario-engine slot), and `lab.wait-for-writ-terminal-xguild` is the
9	 * standalone wait building block — useful for future multi-step
10	 * scenarios where post is detached from wait.
11	 *
12	 * v1 cross-guild surface is shell-out via
13	 * `nsg --guild-root <test-guild> ...`; the real cross-guild engine
14	 * surface is parked at click c-mom9vm3n for v2.
15	 *
16	 * COMMISSION-POST FLOW
17	 * ────────────────────
18	 * 1. Validate givens (briefPath absolute; type defaults to 'mandate').
19	 * 2. Discover the target test guild from `context.upstream` — duck-type
20	 *    detection: any upstream yield with `{guildName: string, guildPath:
21	 *    string}` (the guild-fixture's yield shape).
22	 * 3. Read brief content from briefPath. Title defaults to the brief's
23	 *    first markdown H1 if present, else "Commission from <basename>".
24	 * 4. Shell out: `nsg --guild-root <testGuild> commission-post --title
25	 *    <title> --body <body> --type <type> [--parent-id <parentId>]`.
26	 *    Parse JSON response, extract writ id.
27	 * 5. If `waitForTerminal !== false` (default true), poll until the writ
28	 *    reaches a terminal state. Otherwise return immediately after post.
29	 *
30	 * GIVENS (commission-post)
31	 * ────────────────────────
32	 *   briefPath        : string  — absolute path to the brief markdown.
33	 *   title            : string? — optional explicit title; defaults to
34	 *                                first H1 of the brief, or
35	 *                                "Commission from <basename>".
36	 *   type             : string? — writ type, default 'mandate'.
37	 *   parentId         : string? — optional parent writ id (in the test
38	 *                                guild's namespace).
39	 *   waitForTerminal  : bool?   — default true. When true, the engine
40	 *                                polls until writ terminal before
41	 *                                returning. When false, returns
42	 *                                immediately after post.
43	 *   pollIntervalMs   : number? — only meaningful when waiting; default
44	 *                                5000.
45	 *   timeoutMs        : number? — only meaningful when waiting; default
46	 *                                1_800_000 (30 minutes).
47	 *
48	 * YIELDS (commission-post)
49	 * ────────────────────────
50	 *   waitForTerminal=true:
51	 *     { writId, postedAt, finalState, resolution, resolvedAt }
52	 *   waitForTerminal=false:
53	 *     { writId, postedAt }
54	 *
55	 * GIVENS (wait-for-writ-terminal — standalone)
56	 * ────────────────────────────────────────────
57	 *   writId           : string  — the writ id to poll.
58	 *   pollIntervalMs   : number? — default 5000.
59	 *   timeoutMs        : number? — default 1_800_000 (30 minutes).
60	 *
61	 * YIELDS (wait-for-writ-terminal)
62	 * ───────────────────────────────
63	 *   { writId, finalState, resolution, resolvedAt }
64	 */
